                            <comment id="13128845" author="nkeywal" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2011 13:10:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix by setting the value of &quot;hbase.master.wait.on.regionservers.interval&quot; in the MiniHBaseCluster class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13129295" author="streamy" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2011 22:42:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There was a nice param in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3380&quot; title=&quot;Master failover can split logs of live servers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3380&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3380&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that is in 90 but not 92/trunk.  I&apos;m going to see if we can get that brought into the active branches, then we can just set the maxServers config to the # of RS set to start, and then it will just work instantly w/o having to wait for this interval/sleep loop.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13129553" author="nkeywal" created="Tue, 18 Oct 2011 06:57:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Jonathan: Great, let&apos;s wait for for this more general fix then.&lt;/p&gt;


